Description: In accordance with the CNO approved 2022 PALC Roadmap update, AN/SPN-35, AN/SPN-41,
and AN/SPN-46 systems were planned to sundown upon fielding of the AN/SPN-51 Brizo Landing System. To
ensure Precision Approach Landing Capabilities were maintained on CVN and LHA/LHD class ships through
AN/SPN-51 fielding, continued subsystem development efforts were planned to address emerging system
issues within legacy Radar Landing Systems (RLS) and design / test of system modification kits. With the
2025 cancellation of the AN/SPN-51 efforts, development of system obsolescence mitigations and service life
extensions are critical. Thorough assessments of system obsolescence issues, remaining component service
life, and component manufacturing capabilities are ongoing and will inform specific system modifications. These
research and development efforts will design system modification kits and support various engineering change
proposals to the AN/SPN-35, AN/SPN-41, and AN/SPN-46 as well as the prototyping and testing that ensures
performance and system lifecycle extension to 2040.

B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions, Article Quantities in Each)                                                            FY 2027     FY 2027     FY 2027
                                                                                                                    FY 2025    FY 2026      Base        OOC         Total
FY 2026 Plans:
Design/development of AN/SPN-41 system modifications to implement modified circuit card assemblies (CCAs)
and Field-Programmable Gate-Arrays (FPGAs) that replace legacy hardware that is no longer commercially
available and that support future SW upgrades required to maintain cyber resiliency. Includes development
material procurements and preliminary contractor testing of subsystem modification kits. Legacy system
obsolescence and service life assessments will be conducted that review existing system reliability, parts
availability and manufacturing sources to inform prioritization of system modifications. Initial design and
development work will be conducted for critical obsolescence mitigations and prototype testing will be executed
as prototype equipment is available.
FY 2027 Base Plans:
Complete system design of AN/SPN-41 CCA and FPGA upgrades in support of prototype material procurement
and build. Development of subsystem test plans ahead of subsequent qualification, ground, and flight testing
efforts. Complete preliminary design of AN/SPN-46 Unit 6 and 7 subsystem mod kit supported by component
material procurements and subsystem testing/redesign. Continued design & development of AN/SPN-35
obsolescence mitigations and completion of preliminary design for most critical obsolescence items (e.g. Main
Input/Output Processor (MIOP), and Control-Indicators / Displays).
FY 2027 OOC Plans:
N/A
