Description: In accordance with the CNO approved 2022 PALC Roadmap update, the AN/SPN-51 Brizo
Landing System efforts were initiated to provide for the development, design, integration, and testing of common
equipment upgrades to the AN/SPN-35 and AN/SPN-46 systems. This upgrade was planned to leverage
technology advancements from each system to design a common, modular equipment set that provides
Precision Approach Radar and Automatic Carrier Landing System capabilities to CVN and LHA/D systems, as
required by the AWOTF aircraft. The AESA radar developed in support of the AN/SPN-35 Block II and the and
below deck AN/SPN-46 ECP upgrades are both critical technologies included in the AN/SPN-51 Brizo Landing
System. With the FY 2025 cancellation of the AN/SPN-51 and future year funding reductions, development
efforts will cease upon delivery of data deliverables and a reduced scale prototype.

