                                                              Accomplishments/Planned Programs Subtotals               78.879       0.000      78.378      0.000        78.378$$, $$$$, $$The Acquisition Strategy is to use University Affiliated Research Centers (UARCs), Warfare Centers, and competitive Other Transactional Authority (OTA) agreements
with industry to execute a Rapid Prototyping effort for a new Advanced Lightweight Torpedo split into two increments to deliver partial capability (focused on lethality)
as quickly as possible within the budget in the first increment (INC 1) and full capabilities as defined in the CDD under the second increment (INC 2). This accelerated
approach benefits from stable funding to maintain prototyping timelines.
Scope of effort includes weapon prototyping and testing, launch platform integration, and establishment of all required subsystems and supporting capabilities. Four
OTAs were awarded during the Proof of Design (POD) phase:
(1) Northrop Grumman - Warhead Section
(2) Aerojet - SCEPS Afterbody Section
