                                                                                pment                                          Lightweight Torpedo
 A Rapid Prototyping Proof of Manufacture (POM) OTA contract to an industry Prime is planned for award in FY26 for the INC 1 configuration, which combines the MOD
 2 Forebody
 sections developed in the POD phase with a new INC 1 Fuel Tank and Adapter section and the legacy OTTO Fuel Afterbody, to procure units to support Developmental
 Testing (DT), Warhead and AUR Qualification, Live Fire, and an initial Operational Capability, and to mature the production line for Rapid Fielding procurement.

 In order to meet the operational need for the MK 54 MOD 2 on a compressed development schedule, the program will employ the Middle Tier of Acquisition (MTA)
 Rapid Prototype (RP) pathway per DoDI 5000.80 and SECNAVINST 5000.2G to complete Proof of Manufacture (POM) for MK 54 MOD 2 INC 1 with subsequent initial
 production via a MTA Rapid Fielding (MTA RF) pathway. It is anticipated that POM of MOD 2 INC 2 will also be completed via a MTA pathway, using the forebodies
 produced in INC 1 Rapid Prototyping and if required INC 1 Rapid Fielding. If production numbers escalate the program outside of the MTA limitations (5 years of
 production), then the production of MK 54 MOD 2 INC 1 and 2 will be completed through the Major Capability Acquisition (MCA) pathway with Milestone C completed
 prior to commencement of Low Rate Initial Production (LRIP).

