Remarks
 Product Development funding supports continued capability enhancements and envelope expansion requirements. Major FY27 efforts support further air vehicle envelope
 expansion, engine system safety risk mitigation, risk reduction software development, and Digital Interoperability.

Technical Data Maturation supports non-recurring engineering (NRE) efforts to update and mature technical data required for system integration and future capability
development. Activities include development, review, and validation of engineering drawings, technical publications, manuals, and interface standards to support prototyping,
engineering changes, and system modifications.

Marine Air Ground Task Force (MAGTF) Agile Network Gateway Link (MANGL) has been reidentified as Digital Interoperability (DI) as a capability to enable MAGTF integration
with Joint and coalition networks in support of the Department of War's Joint All-Domain Command and Control (JADC2) strategy. DI represents the capability rather than a
specific system solution, allowing flexibility to evaluate and implement the most effective technologies or architectures to achieve digital interoperability with the Joint force.
Efforts will support development, integration, and demonstration of solutions that enable secure data exchange and operational connectivity across domains and networks




